translation: Thou art the stars; thou art the sky.
Thou art the mountain; Thou art the ocean.10.76.
Thou art the sun; Thou art the sunshine.
Thou art the pride; Thou art the wealth.11.77.
Thou art the conqueror; Thou art the Destroyer.
Thou art the semen; Thou art the woman.12.78.

gurmukhi: ਚਕੰਤ ਚਾਰ ਚੰਦ੍ਰਕਾ ॥ ਸੁਭੰਤ ਰਾਜ ਸੁ ਪ੍ਰਭਾ ॥
transliteration: Chakant Chaar Channdrakaa|| Soubhant Raaj Su Prabhaa||
translation: Thy winsome luster astonishes the moonlight; Thy royal Glory looks splendid.

gurmukhi: ਦਵੰਤ ਦੁਸਟ ਮੰਡਲੀ ॥ ਸੁਭੰਤ ਰਾਜ ਸੁਥਲੀ ॥੧॥੭੯॥
transliteration: Davant Doust Mandalee|| Soubhant Raaj Southalee||1||79||
translation: The clique of tyrants is suppressed; such is the glamour of Thy metropolis (world).1.79.

gurmukhi: ਚਲੰਤ ਚੰਡ ਮੰਡਕਾ ॥ ਅਖੰਡ ਖੰਡ ਦੁ ਪਲਾ ॥
translation: Moving like Chandika (Goddess) in the battlefield; Thou destroyest in an instant seemingly imperishable warriors.

gurmukhi: ਖਿਵੰਤ ਬਿਜੁ ਜ੍ਵਾਲਕਾ ॥ ਅਨੰਤ ਗੱਦਿ ਬਿੱਦਸਾ ॥੨॥੮੦॥
transliteration: Khivant Bij(u) Jvaalkaa|| Anant Gad(i) Biddasaa||2||80||
translation: Thou movest like the fire of lightning; O Infinite Lord! Thy Thorne is visualized in all directions.2.80.

gurmukhi: ਲਸੰਤ ਭਾਵ ੳੁੱਜਲੰ ॥ ਦਲੰਤ ਦੁਖ ਦੁੱਦਲੰ ॥
transliteration: Lasant Bhaav Ujjalan|| Dalant Doukh Duddalan||
translation: Thy Pure emotions gleam; and destroy the forces of suffering.

gurmukhi: ਪਵੰਗ ਪਾਤ ਸੋਹੀਯੰ ॥ ਸਮੁੰਦ੍ਰ ਬਾਜ ਲੋਹੀਯੰ ॥੩॥੮੧॥
transliteration: Pavan Paag Soheeyan|| Samounndra Baaj Loheeyan||3||81||
translation: The row of Thy horses looks graceful; seeing which the horse of the Ocean gets angry.3.81.
